##### Calculus and analysis

[Fourier series](/Fourier_series) approximation of square wave in five steps.

[Calculus](/Calculus), a veritable cornerstone of modern [mathematics](/Mathematics), is fundamentally dedicated to the precise computation of limits, derivatives, and integrals of functions, particularly those involving real numbers. It is the language through which we grapple with the concepts of instantaneous rates of change, the accumulation of quantities, and the behavior of dynamic systems. From this foundational bedrock of calculus, the more abstract and expansive field of [analysis](/Mathematical_analysis) meticulously evolved. Analysis extends these concepts far beyond the familiar confines of real numbers, delving into the properties of functions, sequences, and series in more abstract spaces, often employing rigorous epsilon-delta arguments to establish its truths. It seeks to understand continuity, convergence, and the very fabric of mathematical functions with an almost obsessive precision.

