##### Geometry and topology

[Ford circles](/Ford_circle)—A circle rests upon each fraction in lowest terms. Each touches its neighbors without crossing.

[Geometry](/Geometry), in its most ancient and intuitive form, began as the meticulous study of spatial figures—the familiar circles, squares, cubes, and spheres that populate our immediate physical world. However, over millennia, this field has undergone a profound and considerable generalization, expanding far beyond these initial concrete forms. From this rich geometric lineage, [topology](/Topology) emerged as a distinct, yet intimately related, discipline. Topology takes a more abstract view, focusing on those intrinsic properties of geometric figures and spaces that remain invariant, that do not fundamentally change, even when the figures are subjected to continuous deformations such as stretching, bending, or twisting. It's the study of shape without rigid form, where a coffee cup is topologically equivalent to a donut, both possessing a single 'hole'. This shift in perspective allows for a deeper understanding of connectivity, compactness, and dimension, moving beyond mere measurement to the fundamental nature of space itself.

