##### Information theory and signal processing

[Information theory](/Information_theory) is a sophisticated branch of [applied mathematics](/Applied_mathematics) and, intriguingly, also a significant component of [social science](/Social_science), primarily concerned with the rigorous quantification of [information](/Information). Historically, this field was meticulously developed with the crucial objective of identifying the fundamental limits inherent in compressing and reliably [communicating](/Communication) data across noisy channels. It provides the mathematical framework for understanding the very essence of data, its entropy, and its capacity to be transmitted.

[Signal processing](/Signal_processing), an equally vital discipline, focuses on the systematic analysis, interpretation, and manipulation of various [signals](/Signal_(electrical_engineering)). The signals of interest span an incredibly broad spectrum, encompassing everything from audible [sound](/Audio_signal_processing) waves and intricate [images](/Image_processing) to subtle biological signals such as an [ECG](/ECG) (electrocardiogram), the echoes of [radar](/Radar) signals, and a multitude of other forms. The processing of such diverse signals involves a suite of advanced techniques, including sophisticated [filtering](/Filter_(signal_processing)) to remove unwanted components, efficient storage and precise reconstruction methodologies, the challenging task of separating meaningful information from pervasive [noise](/Noise), rigorous [data compression](/Data_compression) to reduce data volume, and the critical process of [feature extraction](/Feature_extraction) to identify salient characteristics.

*   [List of algebraic coding theory topics](/List_of_algebraic_coding_theory_topics): Using algebraic structures to design error-correcting codes, ensuring reliable data transmission.
*   [List of information theory topics](/List_of_information_theory_topics): A comprehensive overview of entropy, channel capacity, and coding theory.
*   [List of cryptography topics](/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Cryptography/List_of_cryptography_topics): The mathematical principles behind secure communication, ensuring privacy and authenticity.

##### Probability and statistics

The "bell curve"—the probability density function of the [normal distribution](/Normal_distribution).

Main article: [Lists of statistics topics](/Lists_of_statistics_topics)

[Probability theory](/Probability_theory) is the meticulous formalization and systematic study of the [mathematics](/Mathematics) governing uncertain events or knowledge. It provides a rigorous framework for quantifying chance, risk, and the likelihood of various outcomes, transforming intuitive notions of randomness into precise mathematical models. The closely related field of [mathematical statistics](/Mathematical_statistics) then takes these probabilistic foundations and develops the overarching [statistical theory](/Statistical_theory) with an equally rigorous mathematical approach. It is, in essence, the theoretical backbone that underpins all statistical inference.

It is important to note, however, that [Statistics](/Statistics) itself, as an autonomous discipline, is the science primarily concerned with the methodical collection, insightful analysis, rigorous interpretation, presentation, and organization of data. While it heavily relies on [applied mathematics](/Applied_mathematics) and probability, it stands as a distinct field with its own methodologies and objectives, often tackling real-world problems directly where mathematical statistics provides the theoretical tools.

